    <text id="B1199T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Skinner writes regarding an order about the restoration of property belonging to
                    his mother, Clara Skinner, in Norfolk. Both, however, reside in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> O. Brown <abbr
                            expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst Comr</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">Bur. RF
                            &amp; AL</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-10-10"><abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> 10th 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I enclose the <unclear>Memorial</unclear> of Mrs. Clara W. Skinner and the
                    instructions thereon of Major <abbr expan="General">Gen'l</abbr> Howard. I doubt
                    not you will find pleasure in issuing your orders in conformity therewith for
                    the restoration to Mrs Skinner of her house &amp; lot in Norfolk City. I
                    will authorize some friend of hers in Norfolk to call at the office of the
                    Freedmen's Bureau in that city and <unclear>take</unclear> possession for her.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>James H. Skinner</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
